	(27, 'IGME EN GEOLOGY', 'OGC:WMS', 'igme-en-geology', 'The 1:1M Geological Map of Spain covers the Spanish part of the Iberian Peninsula, the Balearic Islands, the Canary Islands, and Ceuta and Melilla (African territories). The Geologic Units are represented in three different layers: Bedrock and Superficial Units, Lithology Units and Geologic Age. An additional layer of faults is also available. For the Geological Age the International Stratigraphic Chart (2006) have been used. The Chronostratigraphic Units included are Erathem and System.', 'http://mapas.igme.es/gis/services/oneGeology/IGME_EN_Geology/MapServer/WMSServer?', 'IGME, oneGeology, Geology, WMS, ', '0;1;2;3', 'IGME EN GEOLOGY;ESP IGME EN 1:1M GeologicUnits;ESP IGME EN 1:1M Faults;ESP IGME EN 1:1M Lithology;ESP IGME EN 1:1M Age', -22.71714, 26.60239, 6.217745, 44.659923, 'Fernando Perez Cerdan', '', 'IGME (Geological Survey of Spain)', 'Rios Rosas 23', 'f.perez@igme.es', 'Madrid', 'Madrid', 'Spain', NULL, '', 'EPSG:4326;EPSG:4258;EPSG:23031;EPSG:23030;EPSG:23029;EPSG:23028;EPSG:4230', 1, '1.1.1'),
